      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "FLYING SOUTH (3) settled near the tail and rounded up her rivals with ease at Mt Barker in an impressive display. He jumped favourite there and returns to his preferred track and trip. Maps for a beautiful run under Staples and if he can run up to her latest figures, he can go back-to-back. HEAD'EM (4) got the job done over 1100m in this grade last time out and that form has already been franked. The wide draw is a query, but Tsang's claim means he remains down in the weights and he has to be included off what he did last time out. FLICK THE SWITCH (2) has been right in the finish all campaign and is knocking on the door of another win. The rise in trip is a slight query, though he rates highly on his recent form and he can be tough to run down once again. PLAY DICE (7) tackled a much tougher race last time out and looks better suited back to this level. SECRET STONES (8) can improve coming back to this level.",
